<h3>Franchise and Multi-Location Management</h3>

Single-location tools break at 5+ gyms. The issues compound:

- Corporate needs standardized campaigns with local customization
- Lead routing must account for territory and capacity
- Reporting must aggregate and segment simultaneously
- Permissions need role-based access control

Kilo specifically built their platform for multi-location fitness brands. Their territory management handles lead routing based on proximity, location capacity, and even staff scheduling. When Location A is slammed and Location B has availability, leads route accordingly.

